                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Mr. Jessup addressed the First Committee on November 23 concerning the British
                    draft resolution of November 18, broadening the scope of the amendments proposed
                    on November 17 by Secretary Marshall in <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss>
                    797, <ref target="#pg_1603">page 1603</ref>; for the full text of his statement,
                    see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December 5, 1948, page
                    687. The official text of the United States amendments to the British draft
                    resolution is printed in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, <hi rend="italic"
                        >3rd sess., Pt. I, First Committee, Annexes</hi>, page 66. The United States
                    amendments were revised on November 25; for text, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >ibid.</hi>, page 67.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
